  "title": "General Ledger Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location:</strong> Joo Koon<br /><strong>Working Days: </strong>5 Days<br /><strong>Working Hours: </strong>9am to 6pm<br /><br /><strong>About Us: </strong><br />A leading offshore oilfield services provider with global operations in over 40 countries. It offers comprehensive services across the full oil and gas lifecycle, including geophysical surveys, drilling, well services, and marine support. Known for technical expertise, extensive fleet, and integrated solutions, the company is committed to safety, sustainability, and continuous improvement.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain full set of accounts including general ledger, accounts payable, accounts receivable, and fixed assets</li><li>Prepare and post journal entries, accruals, prepayments, and adjustments</li><li>Perform monthly, quarterly, and annual closing activities</li><li>Prepare bank reconciliations and investigate discrepancies</li><li>Ensure accuracy of balance sheet schedules and supporting documents</li><li>Prepare monthly financial reports including P&L, Balance Sheet, and Cash Flow</li><li>Monitor and reconcile inter-company transactions</li><li>Maintain proper accounting documentation and filing</li><li>Assist in GST submission and tax schedules preparation</li><li>Liaise with external auditors, tax agents, and relevant authorities</li><li>Support annual audit and ensure timely audit completion</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS) and company policies</li><li>Perform ad-hoc finance duties as assigned by management</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Accounting, Finance, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum <strong>2–5 years of relevant accounting experience</strong></li><li>Experience in handling <strong>full set of accounts</strong></li><li>Strong knowledge of accounting principles and month-end closing process</li><li>Familiar with <strong>Singapore GST, IRAS requirements, and audit procedures</strong></li><li>Proficient in accounting systems (e.g. Xero, MYOB, QuickBooks, SAP, Oracle, or similar)</li></ul><p><br />We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p><strong>Careerstar International Pte Ltd</strong></p><p>EA License No: 03C3254</p><p>EA Personnel No: R23115696</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Chin Lee Wei</p>",
